doctype html
html(lang='en')
  head
    meta(charset='utf-8')
    meta(http-equiv='x-ua-compatible', content='ie=edge')
    meta(name='viewport', content='width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0')
    meta(name='author', content='Manuel Osorio')
    meta(name='description', content='Project Genesis is a css framework meant to be the the starting point for your projects.')
    meta(name='keywords', content='Manuel Osorio, Project Genesis, Css Framework, Genesis, Project, Web Framework ')
    meta(name='robots', content='index, follow')
    link(rel='stylesheet', href='assets/css/project-genesis.min.css')
    link(rel='stylesheet', href='assets/css/app.min.css')

    // Start Social Media Meta Tags
    meta(property='og:title', content='Project Genesis | Css Framework')
    meta(property='og:description', content='Project Genesis is a css framework meant to be the the starting points for your projects.')
    meta(property='og:image', content='https://manuelosorio.github.io/osorio_m_final-project/assets/img/projects/project-genesis/thumb.png')
    meta(property='og:url', content='')
    meta(name='twitter:title', content='Project Genesis | Css Framework')
    meta(name='twitter:description', content='Project Genesis is a css framework meant to be the the starting points for your projects.')
    meta(name='twitter:image', content='https://manuelosorio.github.io/osorio_m_final-project/assets/img/projects/project-genesis/thumb.png')
    meta(name='twitter:card', content='summary_large_image')
    // End Social Media Meta Tags
    
  body
    .nav.default
      .left
        .logo Project Genesis
      .right
        .container
          - list = [{ link: 'index.html', i: 'Home' }, { link: 'colors.html', i: 'Colors' }, { link: 'video.html', i: 'html5 Video' }, { link: '#4', i: 'Item 4' }]
          each item in list
            a(href=item.link class=item.class) #{item.i}
            |
            |
        .menu.default#menu
          .menu-bar
          .menu-bar
          .menu-bar
    .page-content
      .hero
        .hero-container
          .row
            .col.col-12
              h1 Project Genesis
          .row
            .col.col-12
              strong Work in progress CSS framework
          .cta
            a.pg-double-down-arrow(href='#about')
      #about.about
        .row
          .col.col-12
            h2.header What is Project Genesis?
        .row.info
          .col.col-12
            p
              strong Project Genesis
              |  is a css framework meant to be the the starting points for your projects.
        .row
          .col.col-4.col-order-2
            .info-icon
              img(src='assets/img/code.png', alt='project genesis made with sass')
            .row
              .col.col-12
                .info-subtext
                  strong Use Your Own styles
                  br
                  p Don't be shy, add your own styles.
          .col.col-4.col-order-1
            .info-icon
              img(src='assets/img/sass.png', alt='project genesis made with sass')
            .row
              .col.col-12
                .info-subtext
                  strong Made with SASS
                  br
                  p
                    | Project Genesis is modular through the use of 
                    a(href='http://sass-lang.com/', target='_blank') SASS
                    | . Can add your own own modules or remove modules you don't need.
          .col.col-4.col-order-3
            .info-icon
              img(src='assets/img/responsive.png', alt='project genesis made with sass')
            .row
              .col.col-12
                .info-subtext
                  strong Responsive
                  br
                  p Responsive through the use of a grid system.
        div(style='background: #20afab; width:100%; height: auto; padding: 75px 15px; color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85)')
          .row
            .col.col-12
              h2.header Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet
          .row.info
            .col.col-12
              p(style="text-align: left; padding: 0 25px;")
                | Project Genesis is currently being worked and consitently being updated to make the current features functional and more are being added. I'm working on are functional. That being said my plans for this framework is to make it easy to understand while being functional, Although I recommend using the sass version of this framework, I'll also provide a css download link.
                .row
                  .col
                    a(href="https://github.com/manuelosorio/Project-genesis-framework" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer").btn.teal.large.outline.round Github
                  .col
                    a(href="test.zip").btn.lime.large.round Download
      .footer
        .row
          .col.col-12.col-md-12
            p Copyright 2016-2018 Manuel Osorio
        .row
          .col.col-4.col-md-4.col-sm-4
            .logo Project Geneis
          .col.col-4.col-md-4.col-sm-4
          .col.col-4.col-md-4.col-sm-4
            .links
              - list = [{ link: 'index.html', i: 'Home' }, { link: 'colors.html', i: 'Colors' }, { link: 'video.html', i: 'html5 Video' }, { link: '#4', i: 'Item 4' }]
              each item in list
                a(href=item.link class=item.class) #{item.i}
                |
                |
    script(src='https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/3.3.1/jquery.min.js')
    script(src="assets/js/highlight.pack.js")
    script hljs.initHighlightingOnLoad();
    script(src='assets/js/project-genesis.js')
